is closest to the heat.

286
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:46,910
Coupled with rising
temperature on re-entry...

287
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,672
the contact softens.

288
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,956
We could consider
another fastener

289
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:53,359
other than the bolts.

290
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:56,549
Yes.

291
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:58,955
Yes.

292
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,629
There is another opening

293
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,517
in the Engineer
Training Program.

294
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:10,875
Flat head rivets
would reduce wind drag.

295
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:13,759
Mary, a person
with engineer's mind

296
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:15,353
should be an engineer.

297
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,360
You can't be a computer
the rest of your life.

298
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:18,669
Mr. Zielinski...

299
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:20,992
I'm a Negro woman.

300
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,991
I'm not gonna entertain
the impossible.

301
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,639
And I'm a Polish Jew

302
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,711
whose parents died
in a Nazi prison camp.

303
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:29,917
Now I'm standing
beneath a spaceship

304
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:33,038
that's going to carry an
astronaut to the stars.

305
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:36,676
I think we can say we are
living the impossible.

306
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:39,198
Let me ask you...

307
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,793
if you were a white male,

308
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,393
would you wish
to be an engineer?

309
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:46,956
I wouldn't have to.
I'd already be one.

310
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:49,351
Skirts must be worn
past the knee.

311
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,715
Sweaters are preferred
to blouses.

312
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:52,915
No jewelry.

313
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,116
A simple pearl necklace
is the exception.

314
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:58,033
Your supervisor
is Mr. Al Harrison,

315
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,350
Director of
the Space Task Group.

316
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:03,791
You'll write research,
proof calculations, so forth.

317
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:06,758
Do not talk to Mr. Harrison
unless he talks to you.

318
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:10,034
Not many computers last
more than a few days.

319
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,236
He's been through a dozen
in as many months.

320
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,234
Come on, keep up.

321
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:16,233
Things move fast
around here.

322
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,879
Your clearance.

323
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,834
They've never had a colored
in here before, Katherine.

324
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:24,189
Don't embarrass me.

325
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,679
This wasn't emptied
last night.

326
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,558
I'm sorry, I'm not the...

327
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,754
custodian.

328
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:12,429
Excuse me, ma'am.

329
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,636
Mr. Harrison's computer
reporting.

330
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:17,479
Take the desk in the back.
I'll get you work in a bit.

331
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:24,037
Mr. Harrison won't warm up
to you. Don't expect it.

332
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,520
Do your work,
keep your head down.

333
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,280
Thank you.

334
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,512
Go on. Get settled.

335
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:41,840
Paul.

336
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,238
Why are we still
losing shingles

337
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,554
off the heat shield?

338
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:48,075
We're working with a prototype
of the capsule, Al.

339
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:50,056
Its lid is one third the
size of what it's going...

340
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:51,080
I get that.

341
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:54,673
So, what do we do with our
million dollar fan, Karl?

342
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:57,110
Turn it down?
No, Al. I don't think...

343
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:58,669
It was a joke.

344
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,917
Paul, if the heat shield
comes off...

345
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,760
what do you think happens
to our astronaut?

346
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:04,840
I know.

347
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,080
So we're gonna come up
with a solve, right?

348
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,320
Yes, sir.
We're working on it.

349
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,678
Ruth, what's the status
on that computer?

350
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:13,831
She's right behind you,
Mr. Harrison.

351
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,349
Does she handle
Analytic Geometry?

352
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:24,398
Absolutely.
And she speaks.

353
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:25,788
Yes, sir. I do.

354
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:28,558
Which one?
Both.

355
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,199
Geometry and speaking.

356
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,436
Ruth, get me the...

357
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:38,560
You think you...

358
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:41,056
You think you can find me
the Frenet frame

359
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,080
for this data?

360
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,514
Using the Gram-Schmidt...

361
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,676
Orthogonalization algorithm.
Yes, sir.

362
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,479
I prefer it over
Euclidean coordinates.

363
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:53,039
Okay, good.

364
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:56,120
Good, then I'm gonna need
it by the end of the day.

365
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,275
Yes.

366
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,589
I'm also gonna ask you

367
00:18:58,680 --> 00:18:59,760
to check
Mr. Stafford's math

368
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,273
as well as others' on this floor

369
00:19:01,360 --> 00:19:02,429
from time to time.

370
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,600
I can handle that, Al.

371
00:19:03,760 --> 00:19:05,637
I'm sure you can, Paul.
I'm sure they all can.

372
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:07,279
But if that were the case

373
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,976
shingles wouldn't be flying
off the heat shield,

374
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,000
now would they?

375
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,877
Excuse me, could I have
everyone's attention

376
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,029
for a moment?

377
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,639
Thank you.

378
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:20,799
Just to be clear...

379
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,838
in 14 days, the Mercury Seven
will be here for training.

380
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,833
And I have no doubt in my mind
that they're going to be

381
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,831
asking us questions
about our work.

382
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:31,119
I think that's pretty reasonable

383
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:33,236
given we're putting a human
on top of a missile,

384
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:34,440
shooting him into space,

385
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,953
and it's never been
done before.

386
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:38,840
Because it's never been done,

387
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:41,309
everything we do between now
and then is gonna matter.

388
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:44,552
It's gonna matter
to their wives...

389
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,273
to their children.

390
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,080
I believe it's gonna matter
to the whole damn country.

391
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:55,109
So this Space Task Group
will be as advertised.

392
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:58,511
America's greatest engineering
and scientific minds

393
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:00,239
are not gonna have a problem

394
00:20:00,320 --> 00:20:02,754
with having their work checked.
Are they, Paul?

395
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,195
No, sir.

396
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:06,271
Good. So let's have
an amen, damn it.

397
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,440
Amen.

398
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:10,150
Amen!

399
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:11,949
All right.

400
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:42,158
My numbers are spot on.

401
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:46,075
I will double check them, sir.
No problem.

402
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:55,560
Uh...

403
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,776
I'm not gonna be able to...
Work on what you can read.

404
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:00,553
The rest is classified.
You don't have clearance.

405
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,915
These are the numbers
Mr. Harrison gave me.

406
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,036
Yes, I'm absolutely...
Excuse me.

407
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,679
May I ask
where the ladies' room is?

408
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:26,348
Sorry. I have no idea
where your bathroom is.

409
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,639
Yes, sir.

410
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:31,197
Uh, yes, sir.

411
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:03,794
Summertime in
Virginia was an oven

412
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,110
All the kids eating
ice cream with their cousins

413
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:10,834
I was studyin' while you
was playing the dozens

414
00:22:11,920 --> 00:22:14,514
Don't act like you was there
when you wasn't

415
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,318
Runnin' from the man

416
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,628
Runnin' from the badge

417
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:21,155
Don't act like you was there
when you wasn't

418
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:23,158
Runnin' toward our plans

419
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:24,673
And the judges hands

420
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,836
Don't act like you was there
when you wasn't

421
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:31,514
I know they say
you crawl before you walk

422
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:35,113
But in my mind I already jog

423
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:38,638
If I stand still
I cannot get far

424
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:41,436
They want the moon
I'm on Mars

425
00:22:41,520 --> 00:22:46,833
Sometime my mind dives deep
when I'm runnin'

426
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:53,588
Together we'll fly
But no more runnin'

427
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,040
Ruth!

428
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,200
Yes, Mr. Harrison?

429
00:22:57,800 --> 00:22:59,995
Ruth, where's that girl
with the numbers?

430
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:02,276
On a... break.

431
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,435
We take breaks now?

432
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:11,714
Sometime my mind dives deep
When I'm runnin'

433
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:15,400
I don't want no free ride

434
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:18,799
I'm just sick and tired
of runnin'

435
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:25,075
Together we fly
But no more runnin'

436
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:33,514
My God, where have you been?

437
00:23:33,720 --> 00:23:34,869
Are you finished yet?

438
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:36,075
Uh...

439
00:23:36,160 --> 00:23:37,832
Almost. He said
by the end of the day.

440
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,797
The end of the day around
here was yesterday.

441
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,474
I need those done first.

442
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,993
He wants those done first.
Okay.

443
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:45,160
Get going.

444
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:46,429
I'm sorry about that.

445
00:23:47,360 --> 00:23:48,839
Somebody's working on it
right now.

446
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,749
Mr. Harrison.

447
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:59,591
Yeah. Uh, Just set it...
You know.

448
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:04,830
And Stafford's
heat shield calcs?

449
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,992
It's hard
to be sure, sir.

450
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,153
Hard to be sure.

451
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,638
You know
what we're doing here?

452
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:16,191
Trying to put
a man into space, sir.

453
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:17,554
That's right.

454
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,480
That's right. So you can
throw that in the trash.

455
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:21,914
Excuse me?

456
00:25:22,640 --> 00:25:24,596
I said you can throw it away.

457
00:25:25,120 --> 00:25:26,120
Here.

458
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:28,719
It's not an insult
to your work.

459
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,433
It's just obsolete.

460
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:32,830
That's how fast things
are moving around here.

461
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,355
If I said I was sorry,
I'd be saying it all day.

462
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:37,309
What I'm asking you to do,

463
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:38,960
what I'm asking everyone
in that room...

464
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:41,190
all my geniuses...

465
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:43,032
is to look
beyond the numbers.

466
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,876
To look around them.

467
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:47,678
Through them.

468
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:50,070
For answers to questions
we don't even know to ask.

469
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,916
Math that
doesn't yet exist.

470
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,829
Because without it,
we're not going anywhere.

471
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,752
We're staying on the ground.

472
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:00,480
We're not flying into space.
We're not circling the Earth.

473
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:02,358
And we're certainly not
touching the Moon.

474
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:03,714
And in my mind...

475
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:07,275
In my mind, I'm already there.

476
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:10,520
Are you?

477
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:13,229
Yes, sir.

478
00:26:14,160 --> 00:26:15,388
Good.

479
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:16,936
Because I don't need
another smart girl

480
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,188
with an adding machine.

481
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:22,873
Can I go, sir?

482
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:27,958
Yeah, go.

483
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,639
Yes, you can go.

484
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:05,151
We've been waiting for hours.
Next time, you take the bus.

485
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:06,548
She's in a mood.

486
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,837
People talkin'
tryin' to break us up

487
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:15,118
Why won't they let us be?

488
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:17,754
Brick and stones
may break my bones

489
00:27:17,840 --> 00:27:19,831
But talk don't bother me

490
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:23,037
I've been abused

491
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,559
In my heart

492
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:27,555
I haven't been late
one day in 10 years.

493
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:30,359
Haven't been out sick.
Haven't complained.

494
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:31,520
My work's on time.

495
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:32,999
It's done right.
It's done well.

496
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,513
It's not fair,
that's a fact.

497
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:36,193
What's not fair
is having

498
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:37,416
the responsibility
of a supervisor...

499
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:39,237
- but not the title or the pay.
- Mmm.

500
00:27:40,080 --> 00:27:41,229
Watching you two move on.

501
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,997
Now, don't get me wrong.

502
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:46,720
Any upward movement
is movement for us all.

503
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,877
Just isn't movement for me.

504
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,040
Truth be told, Dorothy...

505
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:53,430
I don't even know
if I can keep up in that room.

506
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:56,874
I'll be back with
the computers in a week.

507
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,792
Or out of a job entirely.

508
00:27:58,960 --> 00:27:59,995
Oh, please.

509
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,816
You're better with the numbers
than anyone in there,

510
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:02,920
Katherine, and you know it.

511
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,136
Just make that pencil move
as fast as your mind does...

512
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:06,639
you'll be fine.

513
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:08,677
And you,
have some respect.

514
00:28:08,840 --> 00:28:10,478
Get your damn feet
off my dashboard.

515
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:11,680
This isn't your living room.

516
00:28:16,040 --> 00:28:17,792
I sound like a supervisor,
don't I?

517
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:19,518
A mean old salty one.

518
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:21,511
Riddled with authority,
no question.

519
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:24,752
You don't mess
with Mrs. Vaughan.

520
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,439
Turn that music up.

521
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,120
Good night,
Katherine.

522
00:28:45,240 --> 00:28:46,240
Bye, Kat.

523
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,320
Good night, ladies.

524
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,720
- See you in the morning.
- Bye.

525
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:58,560
Hey, baby.

526
00:28:58,720 --> 00:28:59,789
Hello, Mama.

527
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:03,119
I was fixing to call
the National Guard.

528
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:07,909
Sorry, Mama.
New assignment.

529
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,877
Space Task Group.

530
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:12,031
Oh, my word.
That sounds important.

531
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:13,872
It's a promotion?

532
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:16,873
It might be
a slight promotion.

533
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:18,999
But you want the job, right?

534
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,478
I think so.

