00:29:22,640 --> 00:29:24,392
It's a challenge, but...

536
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:26,636
It's nothing you
can't handle, Katherine.

537
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,238
Thank you, Mama.

538
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:32,909
Are they asleep yet?

539
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:34,712
They're pretending to be.

540
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:37,030
- What are you doing?
- I don't...

541
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,872
They're not pretending
well enough.

542
00:29:38,960 --> 00:29:39,960
Constance!

543
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:41,917
Thank you, Mama.
Love you.

544
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:43,433
This is my bed.
No.

545
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:44,520
Get off!

546
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:45,999
Go back to yours!
I'm oldest! No.

547
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:47,376
- What are you doing?
- Get off!

548
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:48,628
What are you doing?

549
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:51,360
It's not fair how Joylette
gets to sleep by herself

550
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:53,198
because she's the oldest.

551
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:54,793
Yes, it is fair.
No, it's not.

552
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,456
- Yes, it is.
- Nuh-uh.

553
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:58,710
Constance, Kathy, sit.

554
00:30:02,880 --> 00:30:05,030
Now, I understand...

555
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:07,913
you want to be grown
and have your own space.

556
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:10,756
So, whoever sleeps
in that bed,

557
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,472
in Joylette's place...

558
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:14,392
will also do the dishes...

559
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:16,312
take out the trash...

560
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:18,436
and do all of
Joylette's chores.

561
00:30:19,120 --> 00:30:21,429
That's okay. Never mind.

562
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:23,318
Yeah, she's not so
terrible to share with.

563
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,680
Okay.

564
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:28,159
Then don't let me
come home

565
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:30,276
and find you like
this again, you hear me?

566
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:32,908
You're supposed to been
asleep a long time ago.

567
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,593
We just wanted
to say goodnight.

568
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,320
You've been gone
for 300 hours.

569
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,636
I know. I work a
full-time job now.

570
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,313
You all know that.

571
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:48,078
I have to be Mommy and Daddy.

572
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:54,511
I miss your father
just as much as anyone.

573
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:57,475
He's with the angels.

574
00:30:57,640 --> 00:30:59,596
Yes, he's with
all the angels.

575
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:01,432
And he's watching over us.

576
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:03,875
Every minute, okay?

577
00:31:04,040 --> 00:31:06,429
That's why we have
to be strong.

578
00:31:06,520 --> 00:31:07,520
All right?

579
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:08,953
Yes, Mama.
Yes, Mama.

580
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:10,473
Y'all get some rest, okay?

581
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:12,040
Mama?

582
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,120
Yes, baby?

583
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:16,029
Are the Russians fixin'
to attack us?

584
00:31:16,640 --> 00:31:17,789
Where'd you
get that from?

585
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,480
We had to hide under
our desks today...

586
00:31:20,320 --> 00:31:21,389
all scrunched up.

587
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,036
Okay, baby,
that's called a drill.

588
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,679
It means, uh...

589
00:31:25,840 --> 00:31:27,319
you practice safety

590
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:29,789
just in case something happens.

591
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,233
Truth is, we don't know
what they're doing up there.

592
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:36,879
You going to space, too?

593
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,479
No, baby.

594
00:31:38,640 --> 00:31:41,791
But I'm going to do
what I can

595
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,992
to help those brave men
get there. Yes, I am.

596
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:47,993
You could fly up to space
if you wanted to, Mama.

597
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,639
You could be an astronaut.

598
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:51,717
Did you draw this?
Yes, Mama.

599
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:55,031
Is that me?

600
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,200
Mmm-hmm.

601
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,069
You see this?

602
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:01,152
Oh, my goodness.

603
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:02,912
I love you, baby.

604
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,000
I know.

605
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,559
Come here.

606
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:09,075
All right. Now this time
really go to bed.

607
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:10,680
Okay?

608
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:12,558
I love y'all.
Good night.

609
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:13,840
Good night.
Good night, Mama.

610
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,836
I love my picture, baby.

611
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:25,715
Thank you, Lord.

612
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:30,071
- Praise God!
- Praise God!

613
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:32,356
Hallelujah!
Hallelujah!

614
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:35,520
Hallelujah.

615
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:38,359
Praise God...

616
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:42,079
that change is coming.

617
00:32:44,080 --> 00:32:47,390
From the Southern Christian
Leadership Conference...

618
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:49,551
to the good reverend
Dr. King...

619
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:51,039
Amen!
Hallelujah!

620
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:53,395
...to the students sitting in
at lunch counters

621
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:54,480
in North Carolina.

622
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:55,640
That's right.
Yes, sir.

623
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:58,593
His faith in us
has no limit.

624
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:02,596
The good Lord
has our very own women

625
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,398
working on rocket ships.

626
00:33:08,560 --> 00:33:11,597
And we have National Guardsmen

627
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:12,949
defending our freedom.

628
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,395
Give a shout of praise
for Colonel Jim Johnson.

629
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:20,071
Returning home,
by the grace of God

630
00:33:20,240 --> 00:33:22,595
to set up
a National Guard unit

631
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,234
right here in Hampton.

632
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:26,673
Can I get a hallelujah in here?

633
00:33:26,840 --> 00:33:28,831
Hallelujah!

634
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:34,479
I just don't understand.

635
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,633
I don't understand it.

636
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,440
I don't wanna talk
about this again, okay?

637
00:33:38,840 --> 00:33:40,193
A female engineer?

638
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:42,360
A female engineer?

639
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:44,035
We're Negro, baby.

640
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:45,480
Ain't no such thing.
Understand it.

641
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:46,953
It's not like that
there, Levi.

642
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:48,439
You can't apply for freedom.

643
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:51,319
Freedom is never granted
to the oppressed.

644
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:52,993
It's got
to be demanded. Taken.

645
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:54,991
Stop quoting your slogans at me.

646
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:57,795
There is more than one way
to achieve something.

647
00:33:57,960 --> 00:33:58,960
I don't want any greens.

648
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,956
Hey. I tell you
about interrupting?

649
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:02,792
Here. Try this, baby.

650
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:05,880
Yes.

651
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,757
You're gonna eat
them greens, too.

652
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:09,796
Kids need
to eat their vegetables.

653
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,678
You'd know that
if you was ever home.

654
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,951
You better settle down,
Levi Jackson.

655
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,792
Unless you want
this female's mind,

656
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:19,871
right here,
in front of everybody.

657
00:34:21,960 --> 00:34:23,393
All I'm saying...

658
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:25,312
don't play the fool.

659
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:27,311
I don't wanna
see you get hurt.

660
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:29,391
NASA's never ever
given you guys your due.

661
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,913
Having a couple
of extra degrees

662
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,149
ain't gonna change that.

663
00:34:33,680 --> 00:34:35,830
Civil rights
ain't always civil.

664
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:43,152
I don't want
any greens either.

665
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,355
No lip, little miss.

666
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:46,040
Your brother gets them,
and so do you.

667
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:51,395
I hear he's planning
on staying in the area.

668
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,751
Oh, yeah?
Well, that's good for him.

669
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:57,388
Katherine, go find
your way over there.

670
00:34:57,560 --> 00:35:00,597
That Colonel Jim
is a tall glass of water.

671
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,034
That he is.

672
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:04,754
Tall, strong, commanding.

673
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:07,195
And I bet he's like that
day and night.

674
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:09,954
Mary, it's Sunday.

675
00:35:10,120 --> 00:35:11,439
Please have some shame.

676
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:12,874
I will not.

677
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:16,068
Hmm, I think he's
smiling over here.

678
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:17,434
At you.

679
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:23,108
Well I'm not smiling back.

680
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:24,235
Yes, you are.
Oh, child.

681
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,151
You are all teeth right now.
I am not.

682
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,588
Come over here.

683
00:35:29,040 --> 00:35:30,080
He's coming over.

684
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:31,576
Now, why would
he be doing that?

685
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,280
- 'Cause Mary's waving at him.
- No!

686
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,096
Ladies, I'm not ready.
It's too late. Fix your hair.

687
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:36,120
Hello, Colonel.

688
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:38,394
I'm Dorothy Vaughan.

689
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:40,696
That's Mary Jackson.
I believe you met her husband, Levi.

690
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:42,233
Yes, ma'am.
Good to meet y'all.

691
00:35:42,400 --> 00:35:43,753
And Mrs. Katherine Goble.

692
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:45,717
She's not married.
She's a widow...

693
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:48,075
...with three beautiful
little girls.

694
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,240
So well behaved.

695
00:35:49,400 --> 00:35:51,550
Angels on earth is what
we like to call them.

696
00:35:51,720 --> 00:35:53,392
Dorothy, slice of pie?

697
00:35:53,560 --> 00:35:55,073
I'd love one.

698
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:56,719
Excuse me.

699
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:58,056
You already have
a slice of pie...

700
00:35:58,080 --> 00:35:59,080
Uh-huh.

701
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:05,399
I was just, uh, fixing my
three babies some plates...

702
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:06,794
Let me help you.

703
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:08,988
Sure.

704
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:11,151
Fruit salad.
Mmm-hmm.

705
00:36:12,640 --> 00:36:15,518
Pastor mentioned you're
a computer at NASA.

706
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:16,600
Yes.

707
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:17,993
What's that entail?

708
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:19,600
Oh.

709
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:21,911
We calculate
the mathematics necessary

710
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:24,640
to enable launch and landing
for the space program.

711
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:27,309
That's pretty heady stuff.

712
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:28,515
Yes, it is.

713
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:30,398
They let women
handle that sort of...

714
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:31,480
Uh...

715
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,989
That's not what I mean.

716
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,479
What do you mean?

717
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:43,591
I'm just surprised
that something so...

718
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:46,714
taxing...
Mmm-hmm.

719
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:48,313
Mr. Johnson.

720
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:51,635
If I were you,
I'd quit talking right now.

721
00:36:51,800 --> 00:36:53,028
I didn't mean
no disrespect.

722
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:55,554
I will have you know

723
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:57,790
I was the first
Negro female student

724
00:36:57,960 --> 00:37:00,155
at West Virginia University
Graduate School.

725
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,108
On any given day...

726
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,390
I analyze the manometer levels

727
00:37:04,480 --> 00:37:06,948
for air displacement,
friction, and velocity

728
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:09,594
and compute
over 10,000 calculations

729
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:11,398
by cosine, square root...

730
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:13,596
and, lately, analytic geometry.

731
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:14,680
By hand.

732
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,760
There are 20 bright,
highly capable

733
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:19,677
Negro women
in the West Computing Group.

734
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:22,314
And we're proud to be doing
our part for the country.

735
00:37:23,160 --> 00:37:24,160
So, yes.

736
00:37:24,320 --> 00:37:26,709
They let women do some things
at NASA, Mr. Johnson.

737
00:37:27,400 --> 00:37:29,675
And it's not because
we wear skirts.

738
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:32,231
It's because
we wear glasses.

739
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:34,879
Have a good day.

740
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:50,194
Scott, welcome to Langley.

741
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:52,675
Welcome to Langley.
Welcome.

742
00:37:53,520 --> 00:37:55,192
Good to have
you here, gentlemen.

743
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,554
Thank you.

744
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:08,399
That's Alan Shepard,
U.S. Navy pilot.

745
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:10,391
He could be the
first man in space.

746
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:13,239
And that's Scott Carpenter
and Walter Schirra...

747
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:14,958
also Navy pilots.

748
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:17,873
All under 5'11", 180 pounds.

749
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:19,632
IQs over 130.
Mmm.

750
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:21,711
And handsome must be
a requirement too.

751
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:24,599
How could you possibly be
ogling these white men?

752
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:25,760
It's equal rights.

753
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:27,871
I have the right to see
fine in every color.

754
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:32,190
And that's John Glenn.
He's the only Marine Corps pilot.

755
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:34,876
Gentlemen, if we may,
much to see around here.

756
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,960
Well, heck, we haven't
shaken all the hands yet.

757
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:38,640
We have a fairly tight
itinerary, Colonel.

758
00:38:38,720 --> 00:38:39,720
Ruth, he's fine.

759
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,216
He's coming this way.
Look straight ahead.

760
00:38:41,240 --> 00:38:42,240
I'm looking right at him.

761
00:38:42,400 --> 00:38:45,392
Ladies, I didn't wanna run
off without saying hello.

762
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:47,073
Seem to be in a big
rush around here.

763
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:49,151
The Russians certainly
aren't slowing down any.

764
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:50,912
They can't build
a damn refrigerator.

765
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,600
How the heck did they
beat us into space?

766
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,216
And what do you ladies do
for NASA?

767
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:57,800
Calculate your trajectories.
Launch and landing.

768
00:38:57,920 --> 00:38:58,976
You can't get anywhere
without the numbers.

769
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,000
No, sir.

770
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:03,956
Mary Jackson, Mr. Glenn.
Engineering.

771
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:05,576
And I'm proud as the devil
to be working with you.

772
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:06,749
Thank you, Mary.

773
00:39:06,840 --> 00:39:07,840
John.

774
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:10,758
John, let's take it inside.
Yes, sir.

775
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:12,558
Guys.
Nice meeting you guys.

776
00:39:12,840 --> 00:39:14,200
Thank you, Colonel.
Good luck, sir.

777
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:15,599
God bless you all.

778
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:17,794
Thank you. That's wonderful.

779
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:19,600
Thank you!

780
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:51,519
Mr. Harrison wants you
to confirm

781
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:54,319
launch and landing for the
Redstone rocket test.

782
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:02,551
I cannot work on what
I cannot see, Mr. Stafford.

783
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:03,789
It's illegible.

784
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,600
Those numbers have
already been confirmed

785
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:07,557
by two engineers in this
department and myself.

786
00:40:07,640 --> 00:40:09,756
This is more or less
a dummy check.

787
00:40:46,360 --> 00:40:48,360
You have one, we make it two.
Make it double, okay?

788
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:50,197
We gotta get it.
Just make it happen.

789
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:55,235
No one thought to measure
these things?

790
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:57,038
I'm afraid not, sir.

791
00:40:58,440 --> 00:41:00,556
Well, would you
like us to stop?

792
00:41:00,720 --> 00:41:02,711
No. No, just...

793
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:05,794
Actually, no.
Just keep going.

794
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:09,439
In fact, use the
big hammer.

795
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:10,600
Yes, sir.

796
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:12,856
Come on, use the big hammer.
You heard the man. Let's go.

797
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:13,880
Watch out.

798
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:40,920
Ma'am.

799
